 Amcu president, Joseph Mathunjwa says to date no one has taken responsibility for the massacre of the mineworkers. He added that the mining company Lonmin has failed to improve the lives of the mining community as they had promised. “How many houses have been built there at Nkanyeni? No improvement. We made money for Lonmin which is now Sibanye, but there is no improvement to the community; there is no running water; no street lights; there is nothing. They just take the money and leave the country.” In the video below, remembering the Marikana massacre: 